This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=3636

Utility for save files under new names in vim with automatically cleaning up the old file's buffer and hard disk version.

Usage:
<leader>rep brings up the function call. Just enter the desired new filename and press
enter. The new file will be saved, the buffer opened, the old file deleted
if was written to disk and its buffer closed.

default mapping
<leader>rep
